    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Operating EmulatR</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Day-to-day tasks once EmulatR is built and runs: configuring the machine, attaching a console, driving the SRM console, managing storage and snapshots, updating firmware, and turning on logging and diagnostics. Each task has its own topic.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Configuring &amp; Running -- the platform manifest and the ways to launch a run.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Console Connectivity -- the TCP console and the terminal clients that attach to it.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">SRM Console -- the commands available at the prompt.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Storage -- disks, CD-ROM, and the storage devices.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Snapshots -- saving and restoring machine state.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Firmware Update Utility (LFU) -- updating the SRM image in flash.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Guest Boot -- booting an installed guest.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Logging &amp; Diagnostics -- the trace and diagnostic facilities.</li>
    </list>
